All Implemented Interfaces:
org.xml.sax.DocumentHandler, org.xml.sax.DTDHandler, org.xml.sax.EntityResolver, org.xml.sax.ErrorHandler
public class STARTSIntermediateHandler
extends SDARTSHandlerBase

A SAX DocumentHandler that knows how to process starts_intermediate XML. It receives the XML as SAX events. When it is done processing, it will have one or both of the following available:

  • A collection of LSPDocs
  • An HTTPRequest
This class is used by both the WWWQueryTranslator and the WWWSession. When the WWWQueryTranslator uses it, the translator is sending it SAX events generated by the XSL transformation of an LSPQuery into the starts_intermediate form. In this case, the only thing produced is an HTTPRequest. When the WWWSession uses it, the session is sending it SAX events generated by the XSL transformation of an HTML results page into the starts_intermediate form. In this case, there should hopefully be LSPDocs available. In addition, if there was a "more" button at the bottom of the results page, and the www_results.xsl stylesheet was written to find this button and turn it into a starts_intermediate <starts:script>, then a new HTTPRequest will also be available.

When interpreting query results, the STARTSIntermediateHandler is initialized with the set of LSPFields used in the "answer-fields" portion of the query, and it automatically puts only those fields into the LSPDocs; so there is no need to try and do this in the www_results.xsl stylesheet. That file should focus only on the filter and ranking portions of the query.

A new instance of this class should be created each time it is used.

For more information about the starts_intermediate format, see the starts_intermediate.dtd.
